# CSS & HTML Rules

## CSS philosophy
- Plain CSS only. No Tailwind, no styled-components, no Emotion, no CSS Modules unless the user explicitly opts in.
- Co-locate `<Component>.css` next to `<Component>.tsx` and import it at the top of the component file.
- Global styles live in `src/styles/` only: `tokens.css`, `reset.css`, `global.css`.

## Design tokens (mandatory)
All colors, spacing, font sizes, radii, and shadows come from CSS custom properties defined in `src/styles/tokens.css`. Never hardcode them.

```css
/* ❌ Don't */
.button { background: #3b82f6; padding: 12px; }

/* ✅ Do */
.button { background: var(--color-primary); padding: var(--space-3); }
```

If you need a token that doesn't exist yet, **propose it before adding** to `tokens.css`.

## Naming — BEM
- Block: `.card`
- Element: `.card__title`
- Modifier: `.card--featured`, `.card__title--large`

One block per CSS file. The block name matches the component.

## Semantic HTML
- Use the right element. Not `<div onClick>` — use `<button>`.
- Required: `<main>`, `<nav>`, `<header>`, `<footer>`, `<article>`, `<section>`, `<aside>` where appropriate.
- Forms always have `<label for="...">` paired with inputs.
- Headings in order: never skip from `<h1>` to `<h3>`.

## Accessibility (the linter checks; you check too)
- Every interactive element keyboard-reachable (Tab + Enter/Space).
- Every image has `alt` (empty `alt=""` if decorative).
- Every form field has an associated label.
- Color contrast meets WCAG AA (4.5:1 for body text).
- Focus styles visible — never `outline: none` without an alternative `:focus-visible` style.

## Responsive
- Mobile-first. Base styles target mobile, media queries add desktop.
- Breakpoints come from tokens: `var(--bp-md)`, etc.
- Use `rem` for typography and spacing, `px` only for borders/hairlines.

## Animations
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`. Wrap any non-essential motion in:
  ```css
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) { /* animation */ }
  ```
